<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-300] Incorrect maven-bundle-plugin settings cause class duplication in several modules</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-300</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the camel-spring module the osgi.export property is too greedy. Since the maven-bundle-plugin uses ANY resource even if it&apos;s a dependency, by specifying org.apache.camel.component* actually bundles everything under that package from any dependency in the POM, in this case camel-core.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &amp;lt;properties&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;camel.osgi.export.pkg&amp;gt;org.apache.camel.spring*,org.apache.camel.component*&amp;lt;/camel.osgi.export.pkg&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/properties&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be replaced to something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &amp;lt;properties&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;camel.osgi.export.pkg&amp;gt;org.apache.camel.spring*,org.apache.camel.component.event*,org.apache.camel.component.xslt*,org.apache.camel.component.vali&lt;br/&gt;
dator*&amp;lt;/camel.osgi.export.pkg&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/properties&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8212;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The camel-stream component suffers from the same symptom.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
